    slug: "in-quest-of-truth-salman-al-farisi-ra",
    description: `In Quest of Truth: Salman Al-Farisi (R.A) is an inspiring English-language biography of Salman al-Farisi — the Companion of Prophet Muhammad (ﷺ) whose extraordinary journey from Zoroastrian Persia to Islam represents one of the most dramatic and spiritually powerful conversion stories in all of religious history. Priced at Rs.675, this book traces Salman's lifelong search for the true religion — a quest that led him across empires, through slavery, and ultimately to the Prophet of Islam — demonstrating the universality of Islam's message and the profound spiritual sincerity of one of the most beloved Companions.

The book opens with Salman's early life in Isfahan, Persia, where he was born into a wealthy Zoroastrian family. Despite his privileged upbringing, Salman felt an inner restlessness — a sense that the fire-worship of his ancestors could not be the true religion. His quest began when he overheard Christians praying and was moved by the humility and sincerity of their worship. He left Persia against his father's wishes and traveled to Syria, where he studied Christianity under a series of bishops and monks. Each teacher, before dying, directed him to the next — creating a chain of spiritual guidance that ultimately pointed toward the coming of a prophet in the land of Arabia who would revive the pure monotheistic faith of Abraham.

Salman's search led him to Medina — but before he could meet the Prophet (ﷺ), he was captured and sold into slavery. The book narrates this devastating setback with sensitivity, showing how Salman maintained his faith and hope even in bondage. When he finally heard about Muhammad's arrival in Medina, the signs matched exactly what his last Christian teacher had described: the prophet would appear in a city between two volcanic plains, he would eat from food given in charity but not from food given as gift, and between his shoulders would be the seal of prophethood. Salman's verification of these signs and his joyous acceptance of Islam form one of the most emotional moments in the book. The narrative continues with Salman's life as a Companion — his emancipation by the Prophet (ﷺ), his role in the Battle of the Trench (where his suggestion to dig a defensive trench saved the Muslim community), his appointment as governor of Madain, and his continued simplicity and devotion despite holding high office. For readers who love stories of spiritual searching, for new Muslims who see their own journey reflected in Salman's, and for anyone who wants to understand the universality of Islam's appeal, this Rs.675 biography is deeply moving and inspiring.`,
